track_notes: Car park for walkers in Pena. This track is of a circular walk. We tracked for 400m along the defensive rock wall to a marker wall then came back as you can see before continuing to the trig point - this was unecessary. The end of the defensive walk was actually 1m measured (481m) below the height of the summit at the trig point (482m) where I operated from in the end. The Cafe Bar de Grutas at the car park start of the walk offers sandwiches and cold beers at the end of your activation. The cafe in Penina was too traditional for us (locals smoking inside) so we just purchased ice creams and continued our walk back to the cafe in Pena for a pleasant lunch.
track_title: A circular walk including a survey

track_notes: Preferred route west from Grutas Bar and more gradual ascent, heading east on summit. Well signed. Look out for climbers on cliffs to your right on descent track. A fabulous walk
track_title: Route from Car Park at Bar das Grutas
